<P>Augu&s;tus was extremely plea&s;ed at finding her in his power: he &s;ent Epaphroditus to bring her to his palace, and to watch her with the utmo&s;t circum|&s;pection. He was likewi&s;e ordered to u&s;e her, in every re&s;pect, with that deference and &s;ubmi&s;&s;ion which were due to her rank; and to do every thing in his power to render her captivity agreeable. She was
